id="xxix.ii-p3.7"></span>Πιστὸς Κύριος ἐν πᾶσι τοῖς λόγοις αὐτοῦ καὶ
ὅσιος ἐν πᾶσι τοῖς ἔργοις αὐτοῦ. “Faithful is Jehovah in all his words,
and holy in all his works.” Dr. Adam Clarke, after observing that there
is not a verse answering to <span id="xxix.ii-p3.8"></span>נ, *nun*, in
any of the printed copies of the Hebrew Bible, states, that there is one
MS., now in Trinity College, Dublin, which has it thus (he supposes by
correction) at the bottom of the page:

<span id="xxix.ii-p4"></span><span id="xxix.ii-p4.1"></span>נאמּנ יהוה
